Executive Profile
Roy F. Coppedge IIISenior Advisor, BV Investment PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships69--
Background

		Mr. Roy F. Coppedge, III, also known as Copey, is a Senior Advisor of BV Investment Partners. Previously, Mr. Coppedge served as Managing Director at BV Investment Partners. He is a Founder of BV Investment Partners and joined on August 1, 1983. He served as a First Vice President of The First National Bank of Boston from 1975 to 1983. Mr. Coppedge joined the BV Investment in 1975 and headed the Bank’s United States Merchant Banking Group. From 1975 to 1982, he served ... as a Vice President and Deputy Division Head of the Special Industries Division of the Bank, responsible for initiating, structuring and following major lending relationships primarily in the media, entertainment and communications industries. He served as Vice President of American Media, Inc since 1990. Mr. Coppedge has more than 36 years of banking and principal investing experience. He served as a Member of Board of Managers of Harron Communications, L.P. Mr. Coppedge serves as a Director at Smith Media, LLC; EnTouch Holdings, LLC; Vision Communications, SJL Northeast LLC. He served as a Director at Backyard Broadcasting Holdings LLC, American Media, Inc., México Red de Telecomunicaciones S. de R.L. de C.V., Rave Reviews Cinemas, L.L.C., SJL Broadcast Management Corp., Vista III Media, LLC and Television Station Group Holdings, LLC. He has been an Independent Director of Saga Communications, Inc. since June 2013. He is on the Board of Trustees of Belmont Hill School. Mr. Coppedge received an M.B.A. from Harvard Graduate School of Business Administration in 1975 and a B.A. in History from Harvard College in 1970.Read Full Background




